<ns3251:section xmlns:ns3251="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.technologies.java.j2ee.introduction.j2eeApis.jmx">

  <ns3252:title xmlns:ns3252="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">The Java Management Extension (JMX)</ns3252:title>
  <ns3253:para xmlns:ns3253="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    The Java Management eXtension provides a standard API for high-level management of
    resources like initialising them, pausing them, stopping the resource and so on.
  </ns3253:para>
  <ns3254:para xmlns:ns3254="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    Complex, distributed applications and frameworks (such as, for example, the JBoss
    application server) make extensive use of JMX to manage their different components.
  </ns3254:para>
</ns3251:section>